MLRA 26 - Jubilee loam, 0 to 2 percent slopes

report version 0.3

This report requires setting up a selected set in your local NASIS database:

  • load project by name
  • add data associated with MLRA map units into mapunit table
  • add data associated with old and new DMU into data mapunit table

Project Description

"Jubilee loam, 0 to 2 percent slopes" units are in MLRA 26, Carson Basin and Mountains, and are part of the MLRA map unit consolidation (SDJR) project. This mapunit '2w371' , was created for the "SDJR - MLRA 26 - MPC - Jub ilee loam, 0 to 2 percent slopes". It replaced the following mapunits in the following Soil Survey legends:

pmnd 1r0vx 1v6fd

The map unit concepts will be determined from information found in the original manuscripts and from tacit knowledge of soil scientists familiar with the mapping and area. The new DMU(s) will be populated to current standards using existing data, KSSL data, and field notes. These data map units will be reviewed and combined into 1 new MLRA DMU if appropriate. Any map units that cannot be combined during this SDJR project or require further investigation like substatial field or spatial work will be documented and flagged as potential MLRA update projects.
